    "description": "The Goodenough and Fergussoon Islands are in the north-west of the D'Entrecasteaux Archipelago of the Eastern Division of Papua, to the north of their southern neighbours, the Dobu. This entry draws primarily on the ethnographic account by Diamond Jenness, who was assisted by his brother-in-law Rev. Ballantyne, who had spent eight years as a missionary on the island. Their accounts draw from time spent around the Moresby Straits (between Goodenough and Fergusson), and the concentration of settlements on the west side of this channel.",
