    "description": "The city of Ugarit, located on the Syrian coast, is part of the broader region and culture of ancient Canaan. The ports of Ugarit brought it great wealth and made it a vibrant cosmopolitan center, but also a strategic vassal of more powerful kingdoms, namely, Egypt and Hatti. The people of Ugarit were ethnically heterogeneous, with a dominant party of locals, who are mainly responsible for its surviving expressions of religious thought. Although they did not self-identify as Canaanite, a substantial degree of continuity with regional Canaanite culture is reflected, for example, in the onomastics and pantheon of Ugarit. Mythological texts depict El as the chief god and progenitor of the pantheon, while the patron deity of the royal dynasty was Baal. Its cult puts emphasis on the king, who is attended in rituals by priests and singers.",
