    "description": "The Thai Forest Tradition began in the 1920s with Thai meditation master Ajahn Man. He created a new way of practice within Thai Buddhist monasticism, which has been carried on through his disciples until the present day. Two main lineages branched off from Ajahn Man-- 1) his long time attendant and disciple Luangda Maha Bua, and 2) the charismatic teacher, Ajahn Chah, who regards himself as part of the Thai Forest Tradition, although he did not study or live long-term with Ajahn Man. Both Luangda Maha Bua and Ajahn Chah have continued the forest tradition through their disciples, in both Thailand and international countries- primarily the West. Especially Ajahn Chah has been successful in propagating the Thai Forest Tradition among young Western men in Europe, North America, and Australia.",
    "belongs_to_external_poll": false
