    "description": "Wogeo is a volcanic island off the north coast of New Guinea, and previously described a western island of the Schouten group. The people of Wogeo have been noted for their custom of penile bloodletting, which was seen as a form of male menstruation and was believed to be necessary for maintaining good health. the anthropologist Ian Hogbin referred to Wogeo in 1970 ethnography as 'the island of menstrating men'.",
