    "description": "The Mekeo are an Austronesian-soeaking people living on the mainland of New Guinea, nor far from the capital of Port Moresby. In terms of indigenous supernatural belief and the practices, the emphasis in Mekeo culture may be described as more magical than religious (in a Durkheimian sense). Ungaunga (sorcerers) played a major role in maintaining a hierarchical social order.",
