    "poll": 45,
    "description": "Religious precinct in the Forum Boarium, Rome, which hosted twin temples of Fortuna and Mater Matuta from the early 5th c. BCE until Late Antiquity. It may have begun as an open-air cult site, which was followed in the early 6th c. BCE as a small temple with stone built podium; it is not known to which deity this Archaic temple was dedicated. The precinct was radically transformed in the early 5th c. BCE by the construction of a large square platform hosting twin temples of Fortuna and Mater Matuta. These temples were repeatedly rebuilt. At some point in Late Antiquity the eastern temple cella was converted into a Christian church.",
    "belongs_to_external_poll": false
