    "poll": 43,
    "description": "Newar Buddhists as a category delineates primarily Buddhists of the Kathmandu Valley whose scriptural language is Sanskrit and whose spoken language is Newar (a.k.a. Nepāl Bhāṣā). This includes a number of castes, many of whom may employ Buddhist ritual specialists in some cases and Hindu ritual specialists in others. However, it can be said to certainly include the Vajrācarya and Śākya castes, who are the hereditary Buddhist castes known in Newar as Gubhājus and Bares. These Buddhists are organized around hereditary association with monasteries (bāhāḥs) and guild-like socio-religious associations known as guthis.",
