    "description": "Won-Buddhism was founded in 1916 when the Master Sot'aesan Pak Chung-bin (1891-1943) reached enlightenment of the Truth of Il-Won (lit. \"one circle\"). Il-Won is the Dharmakāya (law-body) Buddha and symbolizes the ultimate truth. The Founding Master sought to guide the world toward a new kind of civilization in which the materialistic and spiritual is balanced. He believed that we should find a better way to bring the scientific and spiritual realms into harmony by building a new Buddhism through three main means: edification, education, and charity. Today, Won-Buddhism is a representative Korean religion, and it also has been spreading around the world.",
