    "description": "Vernacular practitioners worship the goddess Śītalā (\"The Cool One\") for their own well-being, prosperity, and health, as well as that of their families and communities. Her worship extends across Northern, Western, and Central India with evidence from the 13th century, but the main textual and ritual context assessed here will be from what is today Bihar, Chattisgarh, Odisha, West Bengal, and Bangladesh.",
